<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-569-910  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 569 910.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  June 18 1990 v7 n25 p4(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Group warns of dire risk to N.Y. from major public network crash.andO;($1 trillion in daily financial transactions threatened by serviceoutage in Manhattan) (New York City Partnership Inc.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wallace, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The New York City Partnership Inc warns of severe disruptions ofdaily financial transactions by a major service outage inManhattan and offers a plan of action for the city, the state, andthe Public Services Commission (PSC).andP;  The group's reportrecommends a high-level task force to create a plan to make thestate's telecommunications network more resilient.andP;  The planshould call for carriers to support firms in key businessdistricts from multiple telephone central offices in order toprotect the companies against cable breaks and central officedisasters.andP;  The state should provide tax incentives for carriersto install alternate and backup lines in planned office parks.andO;The PSC should streamline the current process for introducing newtelecommunications services and revise depreciation schedules toreflect the useful life of equipment.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     New YorkNetworksCommunications IndustryPower FailureDisaster PlanningReportsNew York (State). Public Service CommissionTelecommunications.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>